{
  "text": "Here A : X \u00d7 V \u2192 W * and C : V \u2192 Y are the model and observation operator, so that with the parameter-to-state map S : X \u2192 V satisfying A(x, S(x)) = 0 and F = C \u2022 S, (1) is equivalent to the all-at-once formulation (3), [CITATION_1] . Newton type methods for the solution of nonlinear ill-posed problems (1) have been extensively studied in Hilbert spaces (see, e.g., [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and the references therein) and more recently also in a in Banach space setting. In particular, the iteratively regularized Gauss-Newton method [1] can be generalized to a Banach space setting by calculating iterates x \u03b4 k+1 in a Tikhonov type variational form as",
